Mrs Julia Kraus, Essoldo Fine Arts Ltd., 1 Hobart Place, [London]. Acqua & Terra. Neptune with Horn of Plenty (Aqua & Terra?). Oak panel, 52 x86 cm (Hendrik de Clerk, Kessel, van Thulden, Ambrosius Francken). Said to come from a Dutch private collection. Possibly the whole picture including the figures by Kessel. For the treatment of the background cf. Anonymous Sale Sotheby, July 7, 1976, NÂ° 32: Birds in a North American Landscape (on metal). In background North American Indians & other figures sending fires etc. (repr. catalogue adest). The big turtle (bottom centre) painted blue to a great extent.
